Task 1: Diagram

https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/task-0-blog-post-siham-elani-8rkpe/

Create a diagram that visually represents the process of what happens when the URL is typed in the browser. Tools like Gliffy, Lucidchart, or even draw.io can help you create this.

Start with the browser sending a DNS query.
Show the connection established via TCP/IP.
Display the request passing through a firewall.
Indicate that the request hits a load balancer before being directed to the server.
Highlight HTTPS encryption in the communication.
Show the web server responding and the application server interacting with the database.

